>My usual treatment to remove the fan is to use two claw hammers to  
>pry the fan away from the bracket. I gradually work my way around the  
>perimeter of the fan, and eventually it lets go. This may not be the  
>official approved practice, but it has worked for me OK so far.

This is the approved way to release the fan hub from the press fit of crank:

http://homepage.mac.com/ratwell/.Pictures/AVP/34-RemoveHub.jpg
http://homepage.mac.com/ratwell/.Pictures/AVP/35-Hub.jpg

You can make your own tool using virutally anything that can take the pressure of a screw.

